code: public void testNewWithDatafeedId() {     Exception exception = expectThrows(NullPointerException.class, () -> new GetDatafeedRequest("feed", null)).     assertEquals(exception.getMessage(), "datafeedIds must not contain null values"). }

@Override protected GetDatafeedRequest createTestInstance() {     int count = randomIntBetween(0, 10).     List<String> datafeedIds = new ArrayList<>(count).     for (int i = 0. i < count. i++) {         datafeedIds.add(DatafeedConfigTests.randomValidDatafeedId()).     }     GetDatafeedRequest request = new GetDatafeedRequest(datafeedIds).     if (randomBoolean()) {         request.setAllowNoDatafeeds(randomBoolean()).     }     return request. }
@Override protected GetDatafeedRequest doParseInstance(XContentParser parser) throws IOException {     return GetDatafeedRequest.PARSER.parse(parser, null). }
